1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:03,963
Ask for a “what is missing” section before the research starts.

2
00:00:03,913 --> 00:00:09,721
OpenAI Academy recommends surfacing unknowns, disputed areas, and data limitations.

3
00:00:09,721 --> 00:00:13,865
This is not an apology at the end; it is part of the research product.

4
00:00:13,865 --> 00:00:15,923
Unknowns should be specific.

5
00:00:15,923 --> 00:00:18,548
More research is needed” says nothing.

6
00:00:18,548 --> 00:00:29,230
No current regional churn data was found,” “the two surveys use different age bands,” or “pricing is available only for enterprise plans” tells the decision-maker exactly where confidence is limited.

7
00:00:29,230 --> 00:00:32,221
Define stop conditions for material gaps.

8
00:00:32,221 --> 00:00:45,394
If a key primary source is inaccessible, two authoritative records conflict, or the requested timeframe has no usable data, the researcher should return the blocker and the smallest decision needed to continue, rather than inventing a smooth substitute.

9
00:00:45,394 --> 00:00:50,298
Keep one logical boundary clear: absence of evidence is not evidence of absence.

10
00:00:50,298 --> 00:00:59,298
A search that finds no public incidents may mean there were none, but it may also mean reporting is incomplete, terminology differs, or the relevant records are private.

11
00:00:59,298 --> 00:01:03,060
Attach confidence to the recommendation and name what would change it.

12
00:01:03,060 --> 00:01:11,019
Weak signals, new filings, revised data, or a pending policy decision may deserve a monitoring list rather than a definitive conclusion.

13
00:01:11,019 --> 00:01:14,480
This turns uncertainty into an actionable watch plan.

14
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:18,326
The common failure is hiding gaps to make the report feel complete.

15
00:01:18,326 --> 00:01:22,326
That increases rhetorical confidence while reducing decision quality.

16
00:01:22,326 --> 00:01:26,384
A visible limit is safer and more useful than a silent assumption.

17
00:01:26,384 --> 00:01:31,519
First, require a specific account of unknowns, disputes, and data limits.

18
00:01:31,519 --> 00:01:36,134
Second, use stop conditions when missing evidence could change the recommendation.

19
00:01:36,134 --> 00:01:39,714
Third, state confidence and the evidence that would change it.
